<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/6073</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-24"><hi rend="italic">October 24,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.45
                                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3053. [From <persName>Endicott</persName> to] American Red Cross:</p>
                            <p>1872. Have seen general commanding Archangel area who is now in
                                London. He instructs us not to send foodstuffs to Archangel as it is
                                not necessary.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LIB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>